    "summary": "The Rwandan Civil War began in October 1990 when the Rwandan Patriotic Front (RPF), an organization of Tutsi refugees who had fled earlier anti-Tutsi violence and organized in Uganda, invaded Rwanda from the north. The RPF invasion forced a political crisis in the Hutu-dominated government of President Juvénal Habyarimana, leading eventually to the Arusha Accords of August 1993, which provided for a power-sharing transitional government.\n\nThe Arusha agreement was never implemented. Habyarimana's assassination on April 6, 1994, when his plane was shot down near Kigali airport, triggered the beginning of the [[event:2695|Rwandan Genocide]] within hours. Hutu extremists who opposed any accommodation with the Tutsi minority and feared loss of power launched a systematic campaign of mass murder. The RPF resumed its military offensive and ended the genocide by defeating the Rwandan government forces and capturing Kigali in July 1994, causing the Hutu government and approximately two million Hutu civilians to flee into neighboring Zaire. The RPF government subsequently transformed Rwanda into a stable if authoritarian state under Paul Kagame.",
    "wikipedia_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rwandan_Civil_War",
